'''Sadwaqas Salmen-uly Ghylmany''' ({{lang-kk|Сәдуақас Сәлменұлы Ғылмани}}) or in common '''Saken Qalpe'''  (1890, [[Akmola Province]], near the village Maltabar [[Ereymentau]] - 1972, [[Almaty]]) is a prominent religious and social activist, [[translator]], [[hadith]] [[Muhaddith|collector]] and [[poet]]. He was the [[imam]] of several [[mosque]]s in Ereymentau. In the 1952–1972 years acting [[Qadi]] in Qadiyat of Kazakhstan, was a member of the [[Spiritual Administration of the Muslims of Central Asia and Kazakhstan]].

